name: Issue #61
Challenge Of The Phantom Chief

description: Demo's unique ground-level take on superpowers turns its attention to time travel with "Stranded," a gut-punching story of guilt, abuse, blame and revenge spanning several decades in the life of a woman granted powers she once loved – but might soon regret.
name: Stranded

description: The next chapter in the critically acclaimed and award-winning 'X' trilogy! The Earth is in a state of civil war. Within, the demise of the Celestial at the planet's core has left the world a hollow Earth indeed, with a re-polarization process that will lead to the deaths of every man and woman on the face of the planet. Upon the world, the mutated populace of Earth now seeks to unseat the authority of the heroes who protected and served them in the days when they were only human. Leading them in this charge against the powers that be is Mr. Church - who, unknown to the masses, is Mephisto, the very devil of ancient legend. And in the wake of Captain America's death, the remaining heroes on Earth have rallied around the reborn Captain Mar-Vell and his crusade to bring an end to the power of Death itself. A crusade that will lead to a series of revelations that will unearth the secret of multiple realities, that lie at the heart of the Kree-Skrull War and the very nature of heroism itself. Collecting UNIVERSE X #8-12, X, BEASTS, IRON MEN and OMNIBUS.
name: Universe X, Volume Two

description: Now that Telepath is active again she's ready to take over where she and her parents left off two years ago. Even though it's a whole new world after the New York Disaster it still needs heroes to protect it. She readies herself to return to her crime-fighting ways but she can't do it alone. Will she be able to find enough Uniques who aren't already taken? Can she even make a working team out of them? Or is she only living a pipe dream?
name: Come Together

description: Telepath and her team finally decide to spend some quality time together somewhere that isn't all about training. Why not a friendly game of bowling? Their hang time is cut short, however, by their first real test as a team. Can they take out the monster from the sewers? And who are these people keeping tabs on Telepath?
name: Bowling for Gators

description: In part one of "Ajax," shocking things happened when rifleman Phil Jackson was stationed in Afghanistan. Traumatized by what he lived through, this modern-day Greek hero returned home enraged that he wasn't honored for saving a friend's life after a bloody attack. Now, Phil lashes out at any enemy he can find…
name: Ajax, Part One: The Gods Can Send Such Sickness

description: Telepath's team saves a mall but loose a group of villains. Despite the girls on the loose the team decides to kick up and have fun at a local karaoke joint. All isn’t as it seems, though, as some questions are answered but others are asked. Who are these girls and what do they want with the team?
name: Karaoke Night

description: It looks like the Goth Girls are a larger problem than everyone thought. Kid Quick and Singe start their own investigation to find their missing teammates as the girls do as they like with the team. The Goth Girls have something sinister in mind for the team but can Kid Quick and Singe find out who these girls are and save their team in time?
name: Goth Girls

description: Kid Quick and Singe work to find their friends using whatever means they can. In the meantime the captives try to escape while the Goth Girls are distracted with their plan. Even if everyone escapes they still have to take down the very team that defeated them before. Can they do it? And what are the Girls even up to?
name: Escape

description: Motherboard and her crew spruce up the team's headquarters in time for a surprise barbecue as the team recuperates from their fight with the Goth Girls. The idea of registration floats around but the team shrugs it off as they try to relax. Taskforce and their mystery leader seem to have something up their sleeve. What does this mean for Telepath and her team?
name: Barbecue

description: The police finally stop giving the team leeway about their registration and they have to make their escape after a job well done. Finally everything comes to a head as the team decides what to do about their registration situation. The team totters between breaking up and figuring out what to do. Who will win out, Telepath with registration or Quake against it? Is there any other option?
name: Decision

description: Taskforce finally sets out on their big mission, all members loyal and prepared, despite their misgivings. Meanwhile, the team heads to Washington to figure out what to do about registration. They trip does not go as planned, though, as they interrupt Taskforce's mission. It's Taskforce verses Telepath and her team: no one will make it out unscathed.
name: The White House

description: It’s all-out action as Captain America and the Black Panther wage total war against the Red Skull and his super-powered Nazi platoon. Can their tenuous alliance withstand the onslaught of villainy headed their way?
name: Flags Of Our Fathers part 3

volume.name: Black Panther/Captain America: Flags of Our Fathers

description:
this is a "Fun for all-ages" zombie story, presented in a Convention Exclusive Hardcover.
 
Olive and her little Shih Tzu Otis are on an adventure riding their scooter racing to solve the mystery that's over taken their town.  Zombies roam the streets and its up to her and her little friend to find a cure.
 
Contains Pin-ups created by: Beth Sotelo,  Dustin Nguyen,  Francis Manapul, Joel Gomez , Marcio Takara,  Marcus To, and  Richard Zajac
name: You, Me and Zombie (Convention Hardcover)

description: In their wake lies destruction. Their fierceness knows no end. They are unstoppable. The Infected? No. A Black Ops faction that has their sights set on three travelers. The mindless masses of The Infected are one thing, but how does Selena survive an enemy as patient and cunning as her?

The Uniques Tales are a series of short stories featuring characters and events from throughout the Uniques universe - past, present, and perhaps even future. Check back here the first Wednesday of the month for a new free story by a variety of top indy and mainstream creators.
name: ...As Defined by the Choices

description: The Uniques Tales are a series of short stories featuring characters and events from throughout the Uniques universe - past, present, and perhaps even future. Check back here the first Wednesday of the month for a new free story by a variety of top indy and mainstream creators.
name: Headline

description: The Uniques Tales are a series of short stories featuring characters and events from throughout the Uniques universe - past, present, and perhaps even future. Check back here the first Wednesday of the month for a new free story by a variety of top indy and mainstream creators.
name: The Existence of Angels

description: With nothing to lose, there is only one desperate chance left for the elite Cryptanalysis Unit of the FBI – Special Agent Donald Garner must face his own dark past to save the future of those closest to him! Will Garner’s deepest secrets destroy them all? Or will Stanley finish the job for them?

In the vein of the supernatural TV show LOST! Bram Stoker-award winning writer Christopher Golden and novelist Tom Sneigoski join break-out new art talent Paul Azaceta to tell an innovative four issue mini-series. When flight 654 goes down, it takes 148 souls with it. But not Nicholas Dane. How did the 34 year old college professor survive -- was it a miracle? Now Nicholas finds that he has the memories and skills of one of the passengers from the flight -- a boxer -- and he's got to use them to survive!

The pressure mounts as Nicholas Dane finds himself hunted by operatives that have ties to a secret cabal. What do they know about what's happened to Dane? Meanwhile, Dane finds that he has the ability to box without ever having stepped into a boxing ring! How is he channeling these talents?

Nicholas Dane is running for his life. In this issue a shocking revelation: the men chasing him are somehow connected to the Vatican. Now only his ability to channel the dead is keeping him one step ahead of his shadowy pursuers.

The sold-out mini-series continues! Nicholas begins to channel a new passenger on the plane – someone who knows the secrets of the Cabal that's chasing him, and someone who knows how to fight them! Things turn deadly quickly in a face-to-face showdown, as all the final answers are revealed! More supernatural thrills from the comic that Variety called "Creepy, interesting, and well-executed" and that ignited a five-way Hollywood bidding war!

Prelude to PAYBACK! Punisher: REBORN! In the past few months, Frank Castle has had his family desecrated by the Hood, been killed by Daken, been slashed to ribbons by The Hand, been hunted by Microchip’s Deadly Dozen, and had a bounty placed on his head by Jigsaw. But now, The Punisher has made a list of his own. God help you if your name is on it. It’s time for PAYBACK.
name: Missing Pieces

description:
"Second Chance,""The Older Woman,""Neat Freaked Out!" & "Tree Trouble":
Then, in "The Older Woman," Nancy and Betty both wish they had more time for fun... and thanks to a wishbone, they may get a "Second Chance" to make those wishes come true! Then, in "The Older Woman," a freshman at Riverdale High seems obsessed with Betty! Can Betty's older sister Polly help her lay low or is someone else the true target of his affections? Later, Betty's Mom is "Neat Freaked Out!" at how much effort Betty is putting into cleaning the house... until she learns Betty invited Archie over! Plus, Dilton causes "Tree Trouble" when he tries to help Betty find a new way to declare her love for Archie without having to actually carve their initials in a tree!
name: Second Chance

description:
"Click Trick,""Dog Gone," & "Brush Up":
The hazard blinkers from the roadwork right outside of Archie's bedroom window make it impossible to get a good night's sleep, so Archie turns to the king of sleep, Jughead, to find out the "Click Trick" to a good nights rest. Then, in "Dog Gone," a thunderstorm sends Little Archie's dog Spotty scurrying, leading to a breathtaking adventure as he desperately searches for the petrified pooch. Meanwhile, Archie goes to the woods to "Brush Up" on his still-life painting for art class... but nothing there will keep still!
name: Click Trick

description: Things start to heat up for Nick Walker both onscreen and off. It seems Nick may not be the only one on the set with something to hide, but is this new mystery agent on the side of the angels, or a deep cover Code Black operative determined to bring our leading man down?

The penultimate issue of this summer's hottest indy miniseries! Secret agent/Hollywood heartthrob Nick Walker has one chance to stop the evil machinations of the terrorist organization Code Black, but will Nick's on-screen co-star be a help or a hindrance in this off-screen take down?

Modus Vivendi continues as the Killer begins to understand that for the first time in his career, he has something to lose. His wife, his son, his home; all are threatened by a mysterious and unrelenting client who will push the Killer to the brink. Luckily for the Killer, solving problems is what he does best.

The two worlds of Hollywood star/secret agent Nick Walker are on a full-on collision course and the impact could destroy both his careers. However Nick isn't the only box office draw leading a double life. Will his co-star save his bacon or place it firmly in the fryer?

The epic conclusion on the Legendary Talespinners! Written by James Kuhoric (Dead Irons/Freddy vs. Jason vs. Ash), illustrated by Grant Bond (Igor/Trick R Treat), and art directed by Nick Bradshaw (Danger Girl/Army of Darkness).
name: Hopes and Dreams Are Such Fragile Things

description: Enter an exciting new future with Mega Man ZX! Hundreds of years in the future, humans are able to merge with living ‘biometals’, transforming into Mega Men! But are even the combined powers of the Model Z and Model X biometals enough to take down the sinister Slither corporation?
name: Volume 1

description: Inside the June Alley Inn, located in the western mouse city of Barkstone, mice gather to tell tales, each trying to outdo the other. A competition, of sorts, begins. The game: Tell the best story, get your bar tab cleared! The rules: Every story must contain one truth, one lie and have never been told in that tavern before. Legends of the Guard is a new Mouse Guard anthology series featuring the work of artists and storytellers handpicked by series creator David Petersen. Featured in this issue are stories by Jeremy Bastian (Cursed Pirate Girl), Alex Sheikman (Robotika) and Ted Naifeh (Courtney Crumrin and the Night Things).
name: The Battle of the Hawk's Mouse and the Fox's Mouse; A Bargain in the Dark; Oleg the Wise

volume.name: Mouse Guard: Legends of the Guard

description: Roger Langridge's critically acclaimed run on The Muppets continues. Are the events of this issue really happening? Is it a hoax? An imaginary story? This issue is top secret - but we can tell you it includes an event that Muppet fans have demanded, and will be talking about for months to come!

Queen Sonja craves adventures and she's found it in writer Arvid Nelson's thrilling "Red Queen" story arc! Throw in the beautiful art of artist Jackson Herbert and you'll see just why Queen Sonja is the best fantasy book on the racks!
name: The Red Queen, Episode 2 of 5

description: The city is in absolute chaos as “the woken” tear apart the city in search of those who have killed them. The police have the man responsible for the wakings in custody and he has agreed to send them all back...but under one condition. The tragic origin of Jonathan and Madison Raine is finally revealed and the final chapter of THE WAKING is here! Featuring three incredible covers by superstar artists Joe Benitez (Soulfire), Adriana Melo (Witchblade, Marvel Universe Presents), and a chase (1:10) cover by Tyler Kirham (Fusion, Ultimate Fantastic Four)
name: Part Four

description: With this issue, we debut something so cool, that it's... TOP SECRET! If we told you, we'd have to... lock you into Scrooge McDuck's Money Bin!
name: Mickey Mouse on Quandomai Island, Part 1

description: A new Dark Spirit arrives to spin Cassie Starkweather's crusade in a frightening new direction! Our girl goes wild when Cassie journeys to swamps of the Deep South, and faces the ghosts that haunt the black-water bayous! "A compelling and terrifying ride from start to finish--The Sixth Sense can only wish it had been this creepy." - Cinescape.com

Featuring the guest-art of John McCrea (Hitman, Jenny Sparks), and the introduction of a major new character! Meet Brion, the toughest, cruelest, most unpredictable foe yet to set his eyes on Cassie Starkweather! Who is this wandering demon, and how will he change both Cassie's life and her struggle against the forces of darkness? "ROUTE 666 offers more solid bang for your buck than any other horror comic on the market, bar none." ComicBookGalaxy.com

In their nation's heartland, Cassie Starkweather and Sheriff Cisco seek sanctuary with an enclave of fundamentalist farmers - but the secret they harbor is a supernatural magnet to Cassie's powers of paranormal perception.

The fearsome finale to our haunted heartland story-arc! Cassie and Cisco unravel the shocking secret of the fundamentalist farmers – and then confront the new dark spirit who may prove to be the worst kind of ally!

Featuring guest-pencils by SCION's Jim Cheung! In a creepy coastal fishing village, a waterlogged horror awaits Cassie and Officer Cisco. Meanwhile, bearing down on them from behind is Tanner, the Adversary's ultimate hunter! So what will our psychic sweetie do when she's caught between a Devil and the deep blue sea?
Better red than undead! Cassie and Cisco visit the capital city, and discover that the new ambassador from behind the Iron Curtain is a real ghoul!

Presented for the first time ever, the behind the scenes process of Mack's groundbreaking Daredevil and Alias covers, from initial sketch to finished painting. The secrets behind Mack's art process in the acclaimed Daredevil collaboration with Brian Bendis (including Mack's own photo reference for the characters). Kabuki art process and character designs featuring photo reference of the live Kabuki models. An impressive array of sketches and figure studies in mixed media. A never before seen collection of Mack's cover art for novels and work outside of comics. A sneak peak of David's Noh Character designs for the new Kabuki statues, busts, and action figures.

Behind the Iron Curtain! Cassie and Cisco are kidnapped to the communist state of Rodinia, which has been invaded by the hellish forces of Perdition! Deep behind enemy lines, can our demon-busting duo escape the dreaded headquarters of the secret police?

Better red...or dead? The Cold War gets hellishly hot when the demonic forces of Perdition overrun the communist state of Rodinia! Deep behind enemy lines, can Cassie and Cisco escape the dreaded headquarters of the secret police? "A successful mix of horror and humor!" , Publishers Weekly

The shivering ship of 20,000 cold corpses! Deep behind the Iron Curtain, Cassie searches for the gateway to Perdition. But what she and her small team find instead is a ghost ship trapped in the ice...its frozen passengers just waiting for a warm body to stop by! Brrrrrrr!

This square-bound art book acts as a tie-in to the DVD documentary on Mack's work, THE ALCHEMY OF ART: DAVID MACK from Herovideoproductions.com. REFLECTIONS #12 includes details and commentary on never-before-seen art and stories - including Mack's new children's book THE SHY CREATURES, handmade books and paintings from the DVD. Also featuring step-by-step art techniques, loads of art and extras you've never seen before, figure drawings, new paintings, sketches, Mack's complete story from Tori Amos' new Comic Book Tattoo story, album cover art, large art, live art shows, original scripts, and more!

This is the first self-published release by cartoonist Jeff Lemire. It is a story about a man who lost it all. This is mainly a black and white story with only a little red being used in the interiors.
name: Lost Dogs
